                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1157">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/12–2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Lebanon</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mattison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-21T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 21, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 228:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>427. British Legation informs me that full text of Anglo-French agreement will be
                    released in London and Paris at 3 p.m. GMT and that they are now issuing a local
                    communiqué announcing that talks between British and French military experts
                    began today.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Paris as 108, to London as 15. Sent to Department as 427.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mattison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
